This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a novel active manifold learning method to improve semisupervised manifold learning. The paper also mentions experiments in regression and classification, which are common tasks in machine learning. 

The paper also involves geometric and algebraic methods, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

The use of Gershgorin circle theorem suggests that the paper may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves selecting and labeling representative landmarks, which is a task related to data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
